body:
The following index definition for the `sample_training.companies`
namespace configures MongoDB Search to index only the `country_code` and
`state_code` fields as the MongoDB Search `string` type in the `offices`
array of objects.

Visual Editor

- In the Add Field Mapping window, select
  items from the Field Name dropdown.

- Click the Data Type dropdown and select
  EmbeddedDocuments.

- Disable Enable Dynamic Mapping.

- Click Add.

- Click Add Embedded Field for the
  items field in the Field Mappings
  table and add the following fields by clicking
  Add after configuring the settings for each
  field in the Add Embedded Field Mapping
  window.

  | Field Name | Data Type                                       |
  | ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
  | items.name | Click the Data Type dropdown and select String. |
  | items.tags | Click the Data Type dropdown and select String. |

JSON Editor

```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "fields": {
      "offices": {
        "type": "embeddedDocuments",
        "dynamic": false,
        "fields": {
          "country_code": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "state_code": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
